## 5. Inter-agent communication rule (locked)

A single rule, stated three different ways during the call, never contradicted:

- An agent that needs something it doesn't have → asks **its coordinator**, never another agent, never the orchestrator directly.
- A coordinator that needs cross-domain context → asks **the orchestrator**, never another coordinator.
- Therefore: sub-agents can be built **now**, in isolation, against their own runbooks. Coordinator prompts are "hanging" until the orchestrator is designed, because coordinators are the only layer that talks to the orchestrator.

The orchestrator's exact behaviour when it receives a "missing info" escalation from a coordinator is **part of the flow** and is deferred to §6.

