## 8. Side note — Krell's Campaign Architecture pilot (Abdul's question)

Abdul asked how Krell sliced research topics in the pilot Campaign Architecture runbook. Answer:

- **Research-topic slicing is intentional, not automatic.** Krell selected the topics manually. Reviewing was semi-manual; aggregation was AI-assisted (~4 hours for the full run).
- **Why manual selection matters:** especially now that the Campaign Architecture coordinator's scope has narrowed, the agent must be guided on **which topics to touch and which not to touch**. An unguided agent will sprawl.
- For Krell's pilot, she ran 2 years of data to keep it presentable; her usual default is 5 years.

**Implication for other writers:** when your runbook involves research/aggregation, **expect to define the topic boundary explicitly** in the runbook itself. Don't assume the agent will figure out the right scope from the query alone.

